Download openocd with following git command:
"git clone https://github.com/ntfreak/openocd"

Change to the downloaded directory:
cd openocd

Install it:
./bootstrap
./configure
make && sudo make install

Copy file st_nucleo_f411re.cfg to /usr/local/share/openocd/scripts/board:
sudo cp st_nucleo_f411re.cf /usr/local/share/openocd/scripts/board

Download stlink:
git clone https://github.com/texane/stlink

Change to the downloaded directory:
cd stlink

Install it:
./autogen.sh
./configure
make && sudo make install

Copy UDEV rule:
sudo cp 49-stlinkv2-1.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/

Restart the service:
sudo service udev restart

Now connect your board and then try to connect with openocd:
openocd /usr/local/share/openocd/scripts/st_nucleo_f411re.cfg


Reference:
http://josho.org/blog/blog/2014/11/30/nucleo-gcc/wq

